<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="191" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/2042f</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chinese Minister</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Koo</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 82</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: On July 10, 1918, I had the honor to
                            communicate to you copies of confidential letters exchanged between
                            certain American bankers and myself on the subject of the formation of
                            an American group for the purpose of rendering financial assistance to
                            China.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor now to enclose herewith for your information and for the
                            information of your Government copy of an identic note with accompanying
                            memorandum on the above-mentioned subject, which I have to-day handed to
                            the representatives of Great Britain, France and Japan.<note n="1" xml:id="d191fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_193">p.
                                193</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>